    "visible_text": "White Belt Eleventh Gup White belt at Quantum represents a blank slate. The color white symbolizes snow, emptiness, beginner’s mind. At Quantum, all a White Belt is asked to do is to come to class with an open mind and a willingness to learn. There are two ranks for white belt, and you can tell who has earned a high white because they have a yellow stripe on their belt. In order to earn your stripes, you can participate in one of our regular belt tests. If you want to know what you’re supposed to know in order to test just click on the belt that you are wearing right now. But remember, after you move on to the next level you still have to remember everything that came before it, too. White Belt Curriculum Techniques Basic Form (Key Bong Hyung) High White Belt Curriculum Techniques Kids: One-Steps 1–3 Teens: One-Steps 1–6 Reviews Facebook Community Dojo Quantum Martial Arts is a registered 501(c)(3) nonprofit in the State of California, and we thrive on the generosity of people like you. All donations are tax-deductible. Quantum’s tax ID number is 26-1534597. No donation is too small, or too large. Whether it’s $20 or $20,000, every cent will be hugely appreciated and put to good use. Support Our Kids Donate now to support our youth scholarship program which allows families in need to train at reduced cost. We believe investment in our community involves investing in our youth. Our Sister Schools Our Seattle Dojo has served thousands of students since opening on Capitol Hill in 1995, and currently offers youth and adult classes in the Central District. Our Portland Dojo was established in 2020, and currently offers youth and adult classes in Southeast Portland. A WordPress.com Website .",
